Bug Tracking Application
This is a simple bug tracking application built with Django. The application allows users to report and track bugs in a project.

Features
The application has the following features:

User registration and authentication
Ability for authenticated users to create projects
Ability for authenticated users to create, view, edit and delete bugs within a project
Ability for authenticated users to assign bugs to themselves or other users
Ability for authenticated users to change the status of bugs
A dashboard view that displays all the bugs for a user across all projects
A project view that displays all the bugs for a project
Getting Started
To get started with this application, follow these steps:

Clone the repository: git clone https://github.com/ilmaan/bughunt.git
Create a virtual environment and activate it: python3 -m venv env && source env/bin/activate
Install the dependencies: pip install -r requirements.txt
Run database migrations: python manage.py migrate
Create a superuser: python manage.py createsuperuser
Start the development server: python manage.py runserver
Navigate to http://localhost:8000 in your web browser
Contributing
If you would like to contribute to this project, you can:

Fork the repository
Make your changes
Create a pull request
Please make sure to write tests for your changes.